<item>
            <title>[CXF-1820] CXF does not work with hex-encoded request parameters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-1820</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi, I got a service where I want to expose a resource that is defined by&lt;br/&gt;
an url to a rssfeed, something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    @GET&lt;br/&gt;
    @Path(&quot;/&lt;/p&gt;
{URL}
&lt;p&gt;/&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
    public Subscriber getSubscriber(@PathParam(&quot;URL&quot;) String url) &lt;/p&gt;
{
       ... do something with the url.
    }

&lt;p&gt;Now, this does not work with normal urls, nor with urlencoded urls. Why&lt;br/&gt;
urlencoded values do not work I do not know, but for normal values, it&lt;br/&gt;
seems obvious (they contain &apos;/&apos;s). I&apos;ve also tried base64 encoding the&lt;br/&gt;
urls, but that didn&apos;t work either because sometimes the base64 encoded&lt;br/&gt;
string contains slashes as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After some discussions on the list&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, it was that this is a bug. I have also tested Jersey and standard hex-encoding works with jersey.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Links:&lt;br/&gt;
1. &lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/cxf-users/200809.mbox/%3C48D8F7B9.9090408@scanmine.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/cxf-users/200809.mbox/%3C48D8F7B9.9090408@scanmine.com%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;CXFG using Spring 2.5 and Jetty&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
